<item>
            <title>[SPR-1660] Non singleton ProxyFactoryBean and getBean</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-1660</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve set singleton to false on the ProxyFactoryBean, so my proxied bean should be created on every getObject() (this works). &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But, when using the getBean(String name, Class requiredType, Object[] args) method on the AbstractBeanFactory it seems like it thinks its a singleton because it&apos;s in the singletonCache (the ProxyFactoryBean is always a singleton) but my target bean is not. The problem is that it skips the dependecy injecting stuff and I end up with an un-injected instance of my bean.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
