                            <comment id="16460" author="mgroeneveld" created="Wed, 15 Feb 2006 17:08:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Includes Spring config file for a proxied beans, one singleton and one non singleton.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16461" author="mgroeneveld" created="Wed, 15 Feb 2006 17:15:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It seems there is the freshTargetSource() method in ProxyFactoryBean. When not specifying the targetName but using the target property, the targetSource will always be a singleton. If this is correct behaviour, I suggest adding a warning when parsing the config file if targetName == null and singleton == false (because the first statement always leaves the target a singleton).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
